items.name: Emotion-Puppeteer-LoRA
items.description:
🎭 Emotion Puppeteer - LoRA 🎭

  • Combine with your favorite model to pose facial expressions

  • If you like the model, please post your generations!

  • For stronger effect, use the checkpoint model

Import Instructions

To get what you want, you should read this.

Use this prompt format for best results

  • "{A} face, {B} eyes, {C} mouth, {D}, {anything else}"

  • e.g. "plain face, seething eyes, screaming mouth, closeup portrait, looking away, old man with white hair"

  • CFG = 5 is recommended

A - Face keywords

  • plain, unattractive face - my subjective opinion - biased towards extreme emotions

  • cute, attractive face - my subjective opinion - biased towards pleasant emotions

  • adorable, most attractive face - my subjective opinion - strongly biased towards pleasant emotions

B - Eye keywords

  • seething, >: shaped brows - scrunched brows

  • grieving, <: shaped brows - scrunched brows

  • widening, eyelids raised very high - brows arched

  • glaring, lowered brows - eyelids lowered

  • pleasing, neutral brows - eyes crecent shaped and smile crinkled

  • piercing, neutral brows - eyelids neutral

  • squinting, lowered brows - eyelids squeezed closed or almost closed

  • winking, right eye open, left eye closes

C - Mouth keywords

  • breathing, mouth relaxed and slightly open

  • resting, neutral or slight relaxed frown - lips together

  • smiling, smiling with lips parted - teeth together or slightly apart

  • screaming, mouth wide open - lower-teeth visible or chin scrunched

  • sneering, nose scrunched - left upper-lip raised - upper-teeth not bared

  • singing, mouth wide open and oval-shaped

  • delighting, smiling with mouth wide open

  • kissing, puckered lips

  • gnashing, nose scrunched - upper-lip evenly raised - teeth together - lower-teeth bared

  • gasping, mouth open and frowning-bean-shaped - chin relaxed

  • relaxing, slight relaxed smile - lips together

  • frowning, chin and or nose scrunched - lips together

  • snarling, nose scrunched - upper-lip evenly raised - lower-teeth not bared

  • pouting, slight frown - lower-lip extended

  • grimacing, lips apart and stretched wide - lips apart - teeth may be visible

D - Other keywords

  • extreme closeup portrait, cropped at neck or closer

  • closeup portrait, cropped at shoulders

  • looking straight, head facing forward and eyes looking into the camera

  • looking away, head turned to three-quarters, regardless of eye direction

items.name: goutou 狗头萝莉 Lora
items.description:
This is a LORA for goutou luoli 狗头萝莉. One of China's Most Popular Female Cosplayers.

Trained by ChilloutMix-Ni.

First edition：

This LORA is quite strong as it overfits the training data.

Weight suggestion is lower than 0.8.

Second edition：

一定程度上修正了第一版中存在的过拟合问题，同Korean Doll Likeness进行融合。大家可以更容易地使用本Lora出cosplay角色。

Third edition：Version 2.5

Trigger word: _gtll_

通过大家的返图，我发现V2.0存在过度风格化的问题，即生成图总是有一种滤镜，这个问题可能在风格融合时候不太好用，因此尝试修正。

实际上狗子我训练十几个版本了，由于网上她的图片质量很低，极少高清图片，大部分都是路人返图，这是我制作这个lora最大的困扰。（这也是我想做这个模型的原因，因为想出更完美的照片，而不是网上的低质量照片）

最近我又从几个平台爬了成吨的视频（大部分还是粉丝剪辑发出来的，她本人已经退网删光视频了），这次我从视频帧中提取了一些图片，质量可能比较高。

此外这个Lora我还会继续更新的，希望能有最完美的呈现。下一步我打算找个网络模型从视频提取关键帧，否则几十万帧我根本筛选不了。然后用更高质量的图片作为训练集。

此外，狗子早期和现在是有些区别的，尤其是脸早期更尖，这个大家看一下早期录像就知道了。然后其实我的训练集没有区分都放在一起训练了（早期很多截图什么的质量太差了，近期的比较多）。这次的修正还加大了近期的照片比重，所以脸不会很尖了。

希望大家多多反馈意见和美图，我才能知道优化方向！

我的作品都可以说是个人粉丝向的，所以我还在赶lovelive系列。


All training pictures are from the internet.

Do not use this model in commercials!

items.name: PeachMixs
items.description:
My pixiv

More version on HuggingFace Model Card

My friend model here 😁

About

PeachMixs are various merge models base on a lot of different models. This version can generate good quality illustrations in low steps and have variety of content.

How to use:

  • VAE: anything you want use 😉( but I recommend kl f8 anime, OrangesMixs VAE (NAI VAE) and sd-vae-ft-mse)

  • Prompt: As simple as good.

  • Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (monochrome:1.1), (bad_prompt_Version2:0.8)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Steps: DDIM 50～ , SDE Karass 20～

  • Clipskip: 1 (you can try 2)

  • Upscaler : Latent (nearest-exact)

  • CFG Scale : 5 -7 is good (4～8)

  • Denoise strength: 0.5 maybe

Use model:

  1. AOM2 FP16

  2. Basil Mix

  3. AnidosMix

  4. DosMix

  5. Anything V4

  6. Anything V4.5

  7. Dalcefo

FAQ + other sample/model: Huggingface and pixiv ( will upload later ^_^).

items.name: Mousepad Art - UPDATED
items.description:
UPDATE: V2 IS OUT AND AVAILABLE FOR DOWNLOAD

V2 Log:

Now you can truly and freely create a mousepad of any waifu you want! Newest version is capable of breast, ass, and even crotch mousepad styles!

For V2, I resorted to the laboriousness of cropping, framing, and even making new images from scratch. V1's cropping issue mostly stemmed from all the images being different sizes, backgrounds included. This time, all images, collected or generated, were placed on a blank 1000x1000 canvas so that all outputs during generation would remain consistent in size. Cropping will now only happen if you change the image resolution too much (the further from 512x512 you go, the more it will begin to deviate and distort).

V1 was also incapable of another pose, the legs-up pose, for which on the internet there were not many good training images. The majority of that data for V2 was personally generated by me, and then framed using mousepad templates. Sometimes, when prompting for it, it might put out a pair of mangled-looking legs, but most times it should give you what you want.

Sample prompts were used in the training for this version:

asspad, white background, from behind, ass focus, 1girl, looking back, ass

asspadup, white background, from above, legs up, leg hold, on back, 1girl

boobapad, white background, upper body, portrait, 1girl, breasts

oppai mousepad, white background, upper body, portrait, 1girl, breasts

On very rare occasions, it will completely ignore you and give you a pose you didn't ask for. This seems to be mostly tied to the mousepad token.

THIS WAS TRAINED AS MY FIRST LOCON MODEL, IT WILL NOT WORK WITHOUT IT

Luckily, all you need do is copy-paste the URL to the extensions tab, install and restart, and then load like a normal LORA: https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon

Dataset, cuz there's actually some good shit in there if you wanna use it:

asspad

boobapad

crotchpad

Trained on 140 images, tested across multiple models. Tokens are recommended to keep the AI focused on what you want.

Acceptable compatibility with other LORAs and embeddings.

modelVersions.name: MousepadV1
modelVersions.description:
V1 Log- 2/23/23:

This covers the two most known poses, those being upper body booba style and pov ass focus style, each respectively triggered by "boobapad" and "asspad". Testing concluded that it's ultimately better at getting the latter right, while booba mousepads are a bit trickier. It was trained to provide white or simple backgrounds and to include the whole pad, however, possibly due to differing sizes in the training data, it usually crops the image just slightly, even if neg prompted. You can get an uncropped image if you're persistent enough, though.

Oftentimes, I got the best results usually by using a semirealistic model, and my resolution size was consistently kept at 512x600.

This is only V1 and for now, it does a good enough job to be released. The overall dataset was actually remarkably small despite scouring the internet for as many images as I could. If I remake this, it'll probably with added generation images to help the dataset size.

Trained on 74 images, tested across multiple models. Tokens are recommended to keep the AI focused on what you want.

I don't know what is best, but I do usually use a mix model of Counterfeit & PastelMix, other anime model (Anything, Orange) are compatible.

How to use:

You can input nothing to generate the character any way, but I do recommend you to use following prompts to generate the outfit:

  • Base: umamusume, green bow, green eyes, horse ears, horse girl, ahoge, bow, hat bow, hairclip, long hair, horse tail, hair ornament,

  • Outfit: (white pants:1.2), midriff, navel, bangs, jacket, belt, flare pants, strapless shirt, mini top hat, green shirt, (single sleeve1.4), crop top, white jacket, arm strap, open clothes, open jacket,

    • It isn't designed for alternative outfits, but you can put the Outfit tag in negative prompts for a try, I have put some examples in previews.

    • If you use base prompt only it will be tempting to generate portrait, if so, please add upper body or full body tag.

    • If you find out that it's focusing on chara's feet, you can try to use Controlnet to limit it.

Settings are what I am using, you can change by your own.

  • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

  • about 20 steps, CFG scale 5~7

  • LoRA Weight: 0.6-0.8

  • If using highres

    • ESRGAN_4X (Not good at portrait)

    • Denoising 0.5-0.6.

    • P.S. LoRA training resolution is 768*512.

Columbina (Genshin Impact) - Realistic + Semi-realistic + Anime - LoRA

Making models is costing me my children's tuition. Do you like what I do? Feel free to buy me a coffee 🤗💖

This LoRA was made due to the request of an Anon Discord user and my personal love for the Character of Columbina or Damselette, the 3rd of the Fatui Harbingers. I used NED (Never Ending Dream) as a base model for training. This LoRA was trained on about 70 Images of Columbina since they're aren't that many images of her. I tried either way and it turned out well so I hope you like it.

It's flexible enough to make her in any style (realistic or anime, with a bit of help from style loras for a more dramatic effect) and a few outfits and hairstyle. Please check the examples.

Please be aware that while the LoRA itself is quite flexible with various weights. The Iconic Mask of Columbina will not always work or has a very low chance of working on models other than NED itself.

There isn't any trigger words that specially trigger the LoRA ( I don't know how to do that ) but the LoRA works just fine at a weight of "0.9" but might require tuning based on the model you're using it on. Works great on NeverEnding Dream and with Korean/Japanese likeness loras, or on any anime model out there.

Please enjoy and consider supporting me.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

Consider leaving a ❤️ to receive future updates.

This is a successful experiment I made for testing out my theory on how to make an anime character from a photorealistic dataset. The answer was simply to use NeverEnding Dream (NED). NED was made basically to bridge the gap between photorealistic models and anime ones, so the theory was to use a dataset made of movie screencaps of Jack Sparrow (about 80), tag them with booru style tags (using a combination of WD Tagger + manual) and train a LoRA on NED.
If you then make the inference on NED it gives a perfectly photorealistic model, but if you use it on AnyLoRA or anime models in general it gives you an anime version of Jack Sparrow with little to no style transfer.

You can probably use this technique to turn any real person into an anime counterpart and vice versa (see: my Ganyu LoRA).

You can use at weight 1 generally, but tune it based on the model. Trigger is jack sparrow.

As most of my LoRA's, this can be customized a lot. In the examples I provided a blonde anime girl Jack Sparrow. Examples 6 and 7 are of course using my One Piece style LoRA. Third image by bloodsplash09.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

items.name: Night Sky YOZORA Style Model
items.description:
Night Sky YOZORA Model ——“For ultimate image quality and large image size（>1536 x 1024）”

Trained by @YozoRaAru

如果你需要更好的色彩表现，我推荐你试一下Color Box

If you want better colour representation There is a new style model Color Box

YOZORA is a model that pursues perfection and is filled with personal preferences. I trained it using images that I like, which give it an unparalleled level of detail and completion. It can provide you with very exquisite character images.

In addition to training, I also blended it with dozens of other high-quality models that I personally like, and I tried layer blending as well. Among these models, I selected NovelAI's original model as the major weight because it can give it excellent adaptability to a variety of prompts. I haven't tried testing it with landscape + character yet, but I believe it can also perform excellently in that aspect.

  • For the best results, please ensure that your final resolution > 1536x1024. This is necessary for generating exquisite illustrations

Here are some recommended settings for the parameters:

  • Clip skip: It is recommended to set it at no less than 2. YOZORA already has a rich level of detail, and setting it at 1 may make the image appear cluttered and confusing.

  • Resolution: YOZORA may not be suitable for generating small images because the extreme level of detail may become too crowded. It is recommended do not use Hires.fix to generate large images. A larger resolution is equivalent to a larger canvas, making it easier for YOZORA to capture details. It is recommended to use 1536 x 1024 or higher for Hires.fix.

  • Negative prompts: It is recommended to use EasyNegative to provide brief and precise descriptions.

The name YOZORA means "strolling among the stars in the night sky". I hope that she can bring you the excitement and joy of a sky full of stars on a starry night.

items.name: fking_civitai
items.description:
fking_civitai

A fking StableDiffusion model

Welcome, all you beautiful Civitai people! This model was created directly from the images given by model/TI/lora/etc uploaders for their model samples. The prompt data given from the uploader or PNG metadata was directly used for training, the only curation done was to limit all images to be at least 320 pixels in width or height and less than 1024 pixel in width or height.

Furthermore, all weights and most special characters were removed, such as .:()[] and possibly more (or less, whoops). Any prompt that had a lora, <lora:lora_name:weight> was also stripped. Images were further curated by checking if the remaining tags were > 0.

Current Version v20230318

This version was trained on `42,350 images` for 100 epochs or 4,235,000 steps on RunPod A100 Secure Cloud (ouch, that was expensive).

  • 320 <= image size <= 1024, so try different generation dimensions

  • by <uploader> added to training caption

  • <imagetags>, <triggerwords> added to training caption. (Note: Image tags were scraped on 03/18/2023, and may no longer be accurate, RIP)

  • Text encoder was trained, as a result the training captions from the primarily 1.x training dataset, you'll need to prompt this model as if it were a 1.x model for the best results. If you are not looking for anime be sure to add it to your negative prompts as the training set also contained a large amount of it. (Future version I will be pruning it)

Usage

This model was trained without a trigger word directly with the prompts pulled from previews of models on this site. You can try using it as a general purpose model, or as an experiment. Try and see if you can invoke a certain model's style by using words explicitly in their preview image prompts, likely a trigger word.

Future Updates

I do have plans to update the checkpoint with the newly uploaded images to Civitai, perhaps monthly or bi-monthly, it takes a loooooong time for training and I haven't decided if I want to spend money to off-load it. Next updates will also include a txt file of all images and models used for quicker crediting. I apologize that I didn't have the foresight to do that before I got started.

Upcoming Changes

  • [DONE] Include trigger words as caption data as long as they conform to the tag filters

  • [DONE] Be more precise in caption filter

  • [DONE] Include a credits.txt with version/dataset to quickly identify which image was sourced from what model

  • [IMPLEMENTED] CHAD Score images to further prune the dataset of images with low aesthetic scores. (Implemented in scraper, but not in use on this version)

  • [WIP] Continue ignoring requests for NSFW or 1.x models

StableDiffusion 1.x

There will not be a checkpoint trained against a 1.x base. You are welcome to train it yourself using the dataset I provided.

Contributions

If you are interested in contributing monetarily, please check out the links in my profile, (various charities), or consider donating directly to Civitai. Otherwise, just a thanks is all that is needed.

Additional Notes

I will only be scraping models and images flagged SFW, I will not be training a NSFW or 18+ model, but I also didn't look at each individual picture and some NSFW material may have slipped through.

Remixes/Merges/Extractions

This is Civitai's model, by the people, for the people. Please merge and remix away! I only ask that you DO NOT mix with a model intended for resale, don't keep from your community.

Please remember to like or rate model. Happy prompting!
